# Sprint C16a — op-surreal-ast Mirror

## Goal
Replace format!-based DDL emission in op-codegen-projection with a typed
AST (op-surreal-ast), structurally mirroring surrealdb-core's
catalog::TableDefinition / FieldDefinition / IndexDefinition DDL slots.

## Why mirror, not import canonical
- surrealdb-core::sql::statements::DefineTableStatement is pub(crate)
- catalog::TableDefinition is pub but fields are pub(crate), constructor
  demands runtime IDs (namespace_id, database_id, table_id) + cache UUIDs
- surrealdb-core's full build is heavy (rust 1.95, tokio, async-graphql,
  optional lance/rocksdb deps) — disproportional for "emit DDL"

Mirror is the bridge: typed slots that match canonical shape so a future
`From<op_surreal_ast::TableDefinition> for catalog::TableDefinition` impl
(once C16b adds DDL-friendly setters in the surrealdb fork) is mechanical.

## Public API
  op_surreal_ast::ToSql              — trait (mirror of surrealdb_types::ToSql)
  op_surreal_ast::SqlFormat          — enum (SingleLine | Indented(u8))
  op_surreal_ast::Kind               — Any | Int | Record(Vec<String>) | Option(Box<Kind>)
  op_surreal_ast::TableDefinition    — DDL slots only (no runtime/cache fields)
  op_surreal_ast::FieldDefinition    — DDL slots only
  op_surreal_ast::IndexDefinition    — DDL slots only
  op_surreal_ast::Schema             — top-level container

